URL\/documentation\/WebURL\/WebURL\/pathComponents-swift.property"},{"text":" view.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When modifying this component, the new value is interpreted as a list of path components"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and compacted. The percent-encoding of each path component is preserved,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"although additional characters will be encoded if they are disallowed from this component."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This offers precise control over whether characters are percent-encoded or not,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which may be necessary when constructing certain URLs."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Constructing path strings manually can be delicate. Using the pathComponents view is recommended.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Opaque Paths","type":"heading","anchor":"Opaque-Paths","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If a URL has no host and its path does not begin with a “","type":"text"},{"code":"\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"”, it is said to have an ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"opaque path"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"These URLs look like the following. You can recognize them by the lack of any slashes following the scheme.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["mailto:bob@example.com","└─┬──┘ └──────┬──────┘","scheme       path","","javascript:alert(\"hello\");","└───┬────┘ └──────┬──────┘"," scheme          path","","data:text\/plain;base64,...","└┬─┘ └─────────┬─────────┘","scheme        path"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"These URLs are rather special in a number of ways. Since the path and query components of a URL are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"also opaque strings, every a